SOFTWARE REQUIREMENT SPECIFICATION (SRS)
OpenCart Demo Website ‚Äì Project #1
1. Introduction
The purpose of this document is to describe the functional requirements of the OpenCart demo e-commerce website. This document is created for manual testing and learning purposes.
________________________________________
2. Objective
The objective of this project is to perform manual testing on an e-commerce platform to ensure that core functionalities such as login, product search, add to cart, and checkout work correctly.
________________________________________
3. Scope
The scope of testing includes:
‚Ä¢	User login (invalid credentials)
‚Ä¢	Product search
‚Ä¢	Add to cart
‚Ä¢	View cart
‚Ä¢	Checkout page navigation (no payment)
Out of Scope:
‚Ä¢	Payment gateway testing
‚Ä¢	Performance testing
‚Ä¢	Backend/database testing
________________________________________
4. Target Audience
‚Ä¢	End users browsing products
‚Ä¢	QA testers validating application functionality
________________________________________

5. Functional Requirements
Requirement	Description	Priority	Acceptance Criteria
Login	User should be able to login	High	Error message shown for invalid login
Registration	User can register an account	High	Account created successfully
Product Search	User can search products	High	Relevant products displayed
Add to Cart	User can add product to cart	High	Product visible in cart
Checkout	User can proceed to checkout	Medium	Checkout page displayed
________________________________________
6. User Stories
Login
‚Ä¢	As a user, I want to login so that I can access my account.
Cart
‚Ä¢	As a customer, I want to add products to my cart.
________________________________________
7. Assumptions & Limitations
‚Ä¢	OpenCart demo website is used
‚Ä¢	Payment is not real
‚Ä¢	Manual testing only
________________________________________
8. Conclusion
This SRS document acts as a base reference for manual testing activities on the OpenCart demo website.
